task.summary: Cleaned up code, changed LOTS of statements to final
Pulled CSV reading from vending machine class to separate importer class, added preliminary importer testing class.

Logger removed from menu class and moved into VendingMachine, which cleans up a lot of redundant checks VendingMachine given a return change method to get logger to interact there.
Fixed bug where logger class improperly calculated starting balance after balance we subtracted in VendingMachine
Main CLI switched to a switch statement. It's small enough to not be unwieldy and flows better for reading.

MESSAGE.value: Cleaned up code, changed LOTS of statements to final
Pulled CSV reading from vending machine class to separate importer class, added preliminary importer testing class.
Moved displayItems and purchaseItems menus out of main method and placed in menu class.

Logger removed from menu class and moved into VendingMachine, which cleans up a lot of redundant checks VendingMachine given a return change method to get logger to interact there.

Returns change when exiting program but not choosing finish transaction (instead of keeping change, to keep return customers)

IO Exceptions pulled out of several classes after catch implemented
